-- Korea Electric Power's Unit May Build $1.6 Billion Power Plant in India
-- Shinhye Kang
-- 2010-07-15T02:30:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/korea-electric-power-s-unit-may-build-1-6-billion-power-plant-in-india.html

          
          
             Korea East-West Power Co. may build
a $1.6 billion coal-fired power plant in India, it said in an e-
mailed statement today. The unit of Korea Electric Power Corp.
concluded initial agreement on the project with Sahara India
Power Corp., according to the statement.  
          
          


  


        